{
  "title": "SUBSTRATE MAPPING INVENTORY",
  "form_id": "SMI-7.5",
  "version": "Revision 6",
  "preamble": "This form is administered by Registry Classification Services to individuals who have recently manifested or who have been identified as probable carriers. It is not a diagnostic instrument. It is not a measure of character, intelligence, or potential. The Registry uses the information gathered here to characterize what has occurred, to the extent that characterization is possible.\n\nThere are no correct answers. The questions that feel most uncomfortable are usually the most useful.",
  "instructions": "The instrument contains 55 Likert items, 6 forced-choice items, and 12 experiential checklist items. Most respondents complete it in 30–45 minutes. There is no time limit.\n\nUse the following scale for all numbered items:\n\n- **1** — This almost never describes me\n- **2** — This rarely describes me\n- **3** — This sometimes describes me\n- **4** — This often describes me\n- **5** — This is almost always true of me\n\nFor forced-choice items (marked FC), select the option that more accurately describes you. Not the one you would prefer to be true. The one that is.\n\nFor checklist items (marked EC), check every statement that applies. Each item asks about things you have done or that have happened to you, not things you believe you would do.\n\nAnswer each question as it first arrives to you. The considered answer and the honest answer are not always the same.\n\n---",
